Trampolines.

A trampoline is a pad that launches the player straight up whenever they step or land on it. Walk onto one, or come down onto one from a jump or a fall, and it throws the player upward by a set bounce power before they drop back down. Trampolines are available on 2d and 3d maps only, since a topdown map has no vertical axis to bounce on, and the builder hides the entry on topdown maps.

How a trampoline works.

A trampoline fills a stretch of floor. On 2d maps it spans a range along the x axis at a single floor height; on 3d maps it covers a rectangle on the x and y axes at a single height. Whenever the player is standing on the pad and isn't already in the middle of a jump or a fall, the pad plays its rise sound and launches them straight up by its bounce power in tiles.

When the player comes back down onto the same pad, the land sound plays and the pad rests for its cooldown before it will bounce them again. That pause is what lets the player settle and walk off instead of being flung straight back up the instant they touch down — with a short cooldown the pad feels springy and immediate, and with a longer one the player gets a clear window to step away. The bounce power can't be lower than one and can't be set higher than the map's maximum height.

Trampoline fields.

The trampoline form takes the following:

Coordinates. A minimum and maximum x marking the stretch of pad. On 2d maps a single y sets the floor the pad sits on. On 3d maps a minimum and maximum y mark the rectangle, and a z sets its height.

Bounce power. How many tiles up the pad launches the player. Defaults to 5, can't be less than 1, and can't exceed the map's maximum height.

Bounce cooldown. The number of milliseconds the pad waits after the player lands before it will bounce them again. Defaults to 500.

Trampoline sound (a folder name from the trampoline sounds list, or none). The audio theme; the bundle supplies the spawn, rise, and land clips. Pick none for a silent trampoline.

Auditioning sounds in the builder.

While the trampoline sound list is focused in the form, press space to hear the highlighted theme's land clip, hold control and press L to hear its rise clip, and hold control and press H to hear its spawn clip.

Authoring trampolines by hand.

If you edit main.sif directly, a trampoline on a 2d map is written as trampoline minx maxx y power cooldown tramptype, where y is the single floor the pad sits on. On a 3d map a minimum and maximum y and a z replace the single y: trampoline minx maxx miny maxy z power cooldown tramptype. The power and cooldown are numbers, and the trampoline sound must match a trampoline sounds folder name or the word none.
